f your notice period away from the office, on payroll and receiving contractual benefits of employment.";i:11;s:170:"(also garden leave) in the uk, a period of time after an employee leaves a job when they continue to be paid but are neither allowed to go to work nor to begin a new job.";i:12;s:60:"Validity of garden leave and non compete agreement in india.";i:13;s:160:"Garden leave is typically an arrangement where an employer requires an employee to stay away from work although the employment contract has not been terminated.";i:14;s:169:"Boston (ap) — whether or not they choose to spend their idle time in their yards, workers with noncompete contracts in massachusetts will soon be the first in the u.s.";i:15;s:69:"They can ask you to take any unused holiday during your garden leave.";i:16;s:89:"It is sometimes used to describe a period of paid leave leading up to retiral/retirement.";i:17;s:116:"Garden leave is a notice period where employees are restricted from working but they still get a normal rate of pay.";i:18;s:148:"Xperthr defines garden leave as the practice of requiring an employee not to attend their employer’s premises for work during their notice period.";i:19;s:150:"The aim of garden leave is to keep the employee out of the market place long enough for any information they have to go out of date, or to enable the.";i:20;s:55:"Moreover, under section 27 of indian contract act, any.";i:21;s:78:"{{#verifyerrors}} {{message}} {{/verifyerrors}} {{^verifyerrors}} {{#message}}";i:22;s:164:"In the clause, you can include details such as who they can communicate with regarding leave, what they should expect regarding attendance at the office, and so on.";i:23;s:131:"If your employer says you do not have to be at work (known as 'garden leave') you must get paid as usual during your notice period.";i:24;s:151:"In this short guide, we consider what exactly it is, what practical implications it may have for you, and what your rights are if you are placed on it.";i:25;s:25:"If you're still not sure.";i:26;s:58:"Once in effect, it often prevents the employee from being.";i:27;s:37:"This is called ‘gardening leave’.";i:28;s:84:"This is used when an employee position is no longer needed during the notice period.";i:29;s:135:"In the majority of occasions, employers should include a suitable provision in your contract of employment to allow you to be read more";i:30;s:250:"‘“garden leave” is a colloquial or euphemistic term for an employer insisting that an employee, who has given notice, stay away from work for the duration of the notice period, whilst continuing to pay the employee’s remuneration’, at [84];";i:31;s:196:"The massachusetts garden leave provision states that during the restricted period in which a former employee is barred from working for a competitor, the previous employer must continue paying at.";i:32;s:64:"Instead, the employee is paid their full salary to stay at home.";i:33;s:85:"To enjoy a garden leave provision allowing them to get paid even after leaving a job.";i:34;s:153:"The right to place an employee on garden leave is a contractual one, meaning you should include a garden leave clause when drafting an employee contract.";i:35;s:339:"Without prejudice to the provisions of clauses 4.3 (payment in lieu of notice) and 15.2 (summary dismissal), the company may, once notice of termination has been given by either side require the executive to cease performing his job for such period or periods of the notice period as the company shall in its absolute discretion determine.";i:36;s:270:"The ultimate aim of garden leave is to keep the employee out of the marketplace for long enough to ensure that any information they have will go out of date, or for the employee's successor to establish themselves, particularly with customers, so as to protect goodwill.";i:37;s:235:"Garden leave describes the practice whereby an employee leaving a job—having resigned or otherwise had their employment terminated—is instructed to stay away from work during the notice period, while still remaining on the payroll.";i:38;s:102:"The inference being your employer is paying you to be at home tending your garden rather than working.";i:39;s:95:"An employer can’t ask an employee to go on garden leave unless you both agree (the agreement.";i:40;s:152:"Gardening leave is often used by employers wanting to protect themselves against competition or poaching of customers, clients, or staff by an employee.";i:41;s:93:"There may be further restrictions, and these are included as part of a garden leave contract.";i:42;s:158:"The meaning of garden leave (often known as ‘gardening leave’), is that you require the employee to be away from the workplace during their notice period.";i:43;s:176:"Moreover, during garden leave, the employer is under no obligation to provide work or assign any duties to the employee for the whole or part of the employee’s notice period.";i:44;s:96:"It can only be enforced on you once you have resigned with notice or been dismissed with notice.";i:45;s:291:"A clause to be inserted into an employment contract (for example, standard documents, employment contract for a junior employee or employment contract for a senior employee) or separate agreement giving the employer the right to require the employee to stay at home during the notice period.";i:46;s:245:"Garden leave describes the practice whereby an employee who is leaving a job (having resigned or otherwise had his or her employment terminated) is instructed to stay away from work during the notice period, while still remaining on the payroll.";i:47;s:303:"A garden leave clause should be included in every contract of employment and amongst other things it will strengthen the effectiveness of restrictive covenants.a garden leave clause requires an employee to stay away from the workplace and stop working even though their contract of employment continues.";i:48;s:191:"You must make sure either that the employee’s contract of employment gives you a specific and enforceable right to use garden leave or the employee agrees in advance, preferably in writing.";i:49;s:130:"Garden leave can also be instigated at the employee's request (if it suits you too) or as part of negotiated terms over departure.";i:50;s:51:"An employee is entitled and obliged to attend work.";i:51;s:73:"Garden leave clause implied even though no express contractual provision.";i:52;s:151:"Important employees are sometimes put on gardening leave so that they cannot give private information about their previous employer to a new employer :";}}